narratives.question_text: What knowledge, skills, and insights did you develop by taking this course?
comments: lexicon for discussing the canon of poetry and for analyzing it

By taking this course, I developed a solid background for the reading and analysis of English poetry. I specifically developed skills in metrical scansion, metaphor, and close reading. I also developed my writing skills across the three essays in the course. Through the course, we engaged in a survey of English literature crossing the neo-classical (Pope and Wheatley), romantic (Wordsworth), Victorian (Tennyson and Rossetti), modernist (Eliot), and contemporary (Brooks and Milner) eras of poetry. Through the course, we also developed a notion of an "ars poetica," what it means to write poetry, and what the point of writing poetry is.
Little to none. Other than learning a few throwaway poetry terms, I did not develop as a reader, writer, or thinker. I would recommend taking a course with a professor other than Dr. Levine.
I learned various poetic techniques and styles, poetry analysis, and paper writing.

narratives.question_text: What are the strengths and weaknesses of this course and how could it be improved?
comments:
strengths: amazing and engaging material, prof. levine is awesome

weaknesses: more collaborative projects or discussions would've been fun

Strengths: Great syllabus of poems, nice sprinkling of contemporary poetry, good quick relevant historical lessons 

Weaknesses: None, really, great course!

FEEDBACK - Dr. Levine seems nice overall, but she really struggled there. I was disappointed on how little instruction was geared to actually improving as a reader/writer, especially for this being a foundational English course. As far as strengths go, the couplet and recitation exercises were fun and the class environment wasn't bad at all.

Strengths: The readings were well-selected and well-paced. Discussions were engaging and nicely guided.
Weaknesses: Essay requirements could be a little unclear sometimes.

narratives.question_text: Would you recommend this course to another student? Please explain.
comments: yes! the content is so interesting and prof. levine is wonderful
Definitely! I really enjoyed this poetic survey as I think it really taught me a lot about the art and structure of poetry.
Not with Dr. Levine, no. Her feedback is useless and she's openly disrespectful to her class in front of guest speakers.

Yes, regardless of background or major! The course is set up in a very accessible manner, and though I entered with an interest in poetry, I exited with an even greater appreciation of it. Discussions were fun and thought-provoking; this class felt like a moment of peace in my very hectic schedule.
